# Unity Testing and Regression (Lite)

- Prefer EditMode tests for pure logic and PlayMode tests for scene behavior.
- For each bug fix, add or update a regression check that fails before and passes after.
- Cover success path, failure path, and at least one edge case for non-trivial logic.
- Keep manual test scenarios reproducible (scene, setup, expected result, platform).
- Avoid flaky timing assertions; use deterministic setup and clear tolerances.
